                <head>557. Notes of the Secretary of State’s Staff Meeting, Department of State,
                    September 9, 1957, 9:15 a.m.<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d557fn1">Source:
                        Department of State, Secretary’s Staff Meetings: Lot 63 D 75. Secret.
                        Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_HF1">Fisher Howe</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1957-09-09T09:15:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 9, 1957, 9:15 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>[Here follow a list of those present (23), an intelligence briefing, and
                    discussion of matters unrelated to Uruguay.]</p>
                <p>8. <hi rend="italic">Uruguay</hi>—Mr. <persName corresp="#p_RRRJ1"
                        >Rubottom</persName> said he was extremely discouraged over the poor
                    political situation in Uruguay which is drifting into a potentially dangerous
                    trend. He characterized this as one of extreme complacency, an unsound overdoing
                    of the welfare state and a dangerous penetration of the government by Leftists
                    and Communists. He noted mounting anti-US feeling.</p>
                <p>[Here follows discussion of matters unrelated to Uruguay.]</p>
            </div>
